title: Brazil Ejects Bolsonaro and Brings Back Leftist Former Leader Lula
description: Brazilians voted out their far-right leader, Jair Bolsonaro, after a single term and replaced him with former President Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva.
dc:creator: Jack Nicas
media:credit: Victor Moriyama for The New York Times
media:description: Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva, the leftist candidate who was elected president, on the way to vote in São Bernardo do Campo, Brazil, on Sunday.
